The Telegraph - Calcutta : International
 Tuesday, March 25, 2003 				 Pneumonia spreads in HK
																								Hong Kong, March 24 (Reuters): Hong Kongs hospital chief has been hospitalised with symptoms of pneumonia, fuelling fear that a killer respiratory virus could be spreading faster in the territory than first thought. William Ho, chief executive of the Hospital Authority, was admitted yesterday, a government spokeswoman said. 																								A senior Hong Kong doctor blasted the government for not doing enough to contain the severe acute respiratory syndrome that has killed 18 people worldwide and infected hundreds. 
